\par }\pard {\b\i\f30\fs28 Installation Guides for the System Administrator:
\par }\pard \qj {\b\i\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 First, an appropriate directory to hold the }{\b\f30\fs28 X-CAP}{\f30\fs28  software needs to be created. The installation directory chosen is referred to as }{\f32\fs28 <}{\f32\fs30 xcap_home_dir>}{\f30\fs28 
 throughout this manual. The necessary steps to download the software are as follows:
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par 1. Log in to the target system.
\par 2. Go to the appropriate directory you have previously created:
\par 
\par }\pard \qc {\b\f32\fs28 #}{\f32\fs28  cd <xcap_home_dir>
\par }\pard \qc {\f32\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 3. Insert the distribution tape in the tape device. We assume for this example that the tape device name is }{\f32\fs28 /dev/rmt/0m. }{\f30\fs28 Then type:
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qc {\b\f32\fs28 # }{\f32\fs28 tar xvf /dev/rmt/0m
\par }\pard \qc {\f32\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 The necessary files will be extracted from the system. When this procedure is completed, you will get the system prompt on the screen.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 4. Run the setup script (file }{\f32\fs28 setup}{\f30\fs28 ) and answer all the questions prompted.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 Make sure that a }{\f32\fs28 csh }{\f30\fs28 is invoked
