\par 
\par }{\b\i\f30\fs28 Installation Guides for the User
\par 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 1. Ask your system administrator to copy to your home directory the file }{\f32\fs28 .prepare_xsw.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 2. Make sure that you always operate the software under a csh.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par 3. Insert the command line
\par 
\par }\pard \qc {\f32\fs28 source .prepare_xsw
\par }\pard \qc {\f32\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 in your }{\f32\fs28 .cshrc}{\f30\fs28  file.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 4. Modify the following environment variables to reflect your own configuration:
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
\par }\pard \qj {\b\f32\fs28 XSCIRCUITS }{\f30\fs28 : The directory name where your circuit designs will be stored.
\par }\pard \qj {\f30\fs28 
